  stimulus_text = 'The author of this passage believes that people often think in terms of "either/or" when considering different perspectives. For instance, the author argues, people often think that "if you have strong opinions about something, you''re not open-minded." The author then challenges this assumption by suggesting that "strong opinions can lead to greater understanding."  The passage concludes by stating that "having strong opinions can be a source of strength, as long as you are willing to consider other viewpoints."',
